<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4506] Update documentation to clarify whether standalone-cluster mode is now officially supported</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4506</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;Launching Compiled Spark Applications&quot; section of the Spark Standalone docs claims that standalone mode only supports &lt;tt&gt;client&lt;/tt&gt; deploy mode:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The spark-submit script provides the most straightforward way to submit a compiled Spark application to the cluster. For standalone clusters, Spark currently only supports deploying the driver inside the client process that is submitting the application (client deploy mode).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like &lt;tt&gt;standalone-cluster&lt;/tt&gt; mode actually works (I&apos;ve used it and have heard from users that are successfully using it, too).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current line was added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2259&quot; title=&quot;Spark submit documentation for --deploy-mode is highly misleading&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-2259&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-2259&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;tt&gt;standalone-cluster&lt;/tt&gt; mode wasn&apos;t officially supported.  It looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2260&quot; title=&quot;Spark submit standalone-cluster mode is broken&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-2260&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-2260&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed a number of bugs in &lt;tt&gt;standalone-cluster&lt;/tt&gt; mode, so we should update the documentation if we&apos;re now ready to officially support it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
